---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Badge from '../../components/Badge.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { Badge } from 'comet-astro';

---

<Badge label="Launch ready" variant="success" />`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Badge"
  description="Compact status label with AAA contrast across light and dark mode."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Badges call out short states or categories without overpowering
      surrounding copy. Each variant uses a high-contrast palette that meets
      WCAG AAA for small text in both themes, so the label remains legible even
      inside dense tables or cards.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Drop badges inline with headings, lists, or buttons. Prefix a status,
      highlight an availability window, or draw attention to experimental
      features without introducing a full alert.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          label
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Text content of the badge. Keep it briefâ€”typically a single word or
          short phrase.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          variant?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Visual theme for the badge. Choose among <code>neutral</code>, <code
            >primary</code
          >, <code>success</code>, <code>warning</code>, or <code>danger</code>.
          Defaults to <code>neutral</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm sm:col-span-2"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          className?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Extra Tailwind utilities appended to the badge. Useful for adding
          margins, uppercase transforms, or custom tracking to match your
          typography.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component, pass the label, and optionally choose a variant. The
      badge automatically swaps palettes in dark mode to maintain AAA contrast,
      so you can rely on the defaults without hand-tuning colors.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Variants</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
      <Badge label="Neutral" variant="neutral" />
      <Badge label="Primary" variant="primary" />
      <Badge label="Success" variant="success" />
      <Badge label="Warning" variant="warning" />
      <Badge label="Danger" variant="danger" />
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
      Each variant pairs a deep tone in light mode with a light counterpart in
      dark mode, ensuring the 12&nbsp;px text remains legible everywhere.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      AAA contrast is built in: we target at least a 9:1 ratio between
      background and text in both themes. Because badges often appear next to
      other interactive controls, keeping them readable helps everyone parse
      statuses quickly.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      When translating UI strings, provide localized labels so assistive
      technology users hear the same wording as sighted visitors. The component
      renders a plain <code>span</code>, so no extra roles are required.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Examples</h2>

    <article class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          Inline with headings
        </h3>
        <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
          Append a badge to release notes or API titles to quickly call out
          lifecycle information. Add a small margin utility to keep the spacing
          balanced.
        </p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
        v3.1 Launch Notes
        <Badge label="Stable" variant="success" className="ml-3" />
      </h4>
    </article>

    <article class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Grouped legends</h3>
        <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
          Combine multiple badges to create a compact legend. The consistent
          sizing keeps alignment tidy without extra wrappers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
        <Badge label="Alpha" variant="warning" />
        <Badge label="Live" variant="primary" />
        <Badge label="Limited" variant="danger" />
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
